  "prompt": "What universities does Viad recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Viad Corporation, a prominent provider of construction materials and services, actively recruits new graduates to support its various operations across regions such as Indiana and Florida. While specific recruitment practices and targeted universities can evolve over time, here's a general overview based on available information up to October 2023:\n\n### **Universities Viad May Recruit From**\n\nViad typically targets universities with strong programs in engineering, construction management, business, and related fields. While the company may have partnerships or active recruitment events at specific institutions, some of the universities they are likely to engage with include:\n\n1. **Indiana University Bloomington (IU)**\n2. **Purdue University**\n3. **University of Notre Dame**\n4. **Valparaiso University**\n5. **Florida State University (FSU)**\n6. **University of Central Florida (UCF)**\n7. **Florida International University (FIU)**\n\nAdditionally, Viad may also consider graduates from other reputable institutions, especially those located near their operational regions or those with specialized programs relevant to Viad\u2019s business areas.\n\n### **Majors and Fields of Study Viad Typically Looks For**\n\nViad recruits a diverse range of majors to support its multifaceted operations. Some of the key fields of study they may be interested in include:\n\n1. **Civil Engineering**: For roles in infrastructure design, construction management, and project engineering.\n2. **Construction Management**: Focused on overseeing construction projects, ensuring they are completed on time and within budget.\n3. **Business Administration/Management**: For roles in operations, finance, human resources, and strategic planning.\n4. **Environmental Engineering/Science**: To manage sustainability initiatives and comply with environmental regulations.\n5. **Mechanical Engineering**: Supporting equipment maintenance, machinery design, and operational efficiency.\n6. **Information Technology (IT) and Computer Science**: For roles in managing IT infrastructure, software development, and data analysis.\n7. **Finance and Accounting**: Handling budgeting, financial planning, and analysis to support the company's financial health.\n8. **Supply Chain Management**: Overseeing the procurement, logistics, and distribution of materials and services.\n9. **Health and Safety**: Ensuring workplace safety standards are met and maintained across all projects.\n\n### **How to Increase Your Chances of Being Recruited by Viad**\n\n- **Internships and Co-ops**: Gaining practical experience through internships can make you a more attractive candidate.\n- **Campus Recruiting Events**: Attend career fairs and networking events where Viad representatives may be present.\n- **Relevant Coursework and Projects**: Engage in projects or coursework that align with Viad\u2019s business areas.\n- **Professional Certifications**: Obtaining certifications related to your field can demonstrate commitment and expertise.\n- **Strong Academic Performance**: Maintaining a solid GPA and showcasing academic achievements can enhance your candidacy.\n\n### **Staying Updated**\n\nRecruitment strategies and targeted universities can change based on Viad\u2019s evolving business needs and market conditions. To get the most accurate and up-to-date information:\n\n- **Visit Viad\u2019s Official Careers Page**: [Viad Careers](https://www.viad.com/careers) (ensure to verify the exact URL)\n- **Connect on Professional Networks**: Platforms like LinkedIn can provide insights into Viad\u2019s recruitment activities and employee backgrounds.\n- **Reach Out Directly**: Contact Viad\u2019s HR or recruitment team for specific inquiries about recruitment partners and preferred majors.\n\nBy aligning your educational background and career aspirations with Viad\u2019s needs, you can enhance your prospects of securing a position within the company.",
